---
name: {{ name | tojson }}
description: {{ description | tojson }}
kind: meta
meta_priority: {{ meta_priority | default(50) }}
always: false
triggers:
{%- for t in triggers %}
  - {{ t | tojson }}
{%- endfor %}
provenance:
  origin: opensquilla-user
  license: Apache-2.0
metadata:
  opensquilla:
    risk: "low"
    read_only: true
    no_write: true
    write_access: false
    network_access: false
    creator_gates:
      - "G1 structural lint"
      - "G2 scheduler dry-run"
      - "G3 positive trigger smoke"
      - "G4 unrelated negative smoke"
      - "acceptance_compare versus highest-tier no-meta baseline"
      - "runtime_e2e versus highest-tier no-meta baseline"
composition:
  steps:
{%- for b in branches %}
    - id: {{ b.id }}
{%- if creator_step_kind is defined %}
{%- set branch_kind = creator_step_kind(b.skill) %}
{%- else %}
{%- set branch_kind = "agent" %}
{%- endif %}
{%- if branch_kind in ["skill_exec", "llm_chat"] %}
      kind: {{ branch_kind }}
{%- endif %}
      skill: {{ b.skill | tojson }}
      read_only: true
      write_access: false
      network_access: false
      with:
{%- if b.with_keys %}
{%- for k, v in b.with_keys.items() %}
        {{ k }}: {{ v | tojson }}
{%- endfor %}
{%- elif branch_kind == "skill_exec" and b.skill == "history-explorer" %}
        query: "{{ b.task }}: {{ '{{' }} inputs.user_message | xml_escape | truncate(512) {{ '}}' }}"
        window_days: "30"
        include: "co_occurrences,meta_usage"
{%- elif branch_kind == "skill_exec" and b.skill == "git-diff" %}
        mode: cached_fallback_worktree
        cwd: "{{ '{{' }} inputs.workspace_dir | default('.') {{ '}}' }}"
{%- else %}
        task: "{{ b.task }}: {{ '{{' }} inputs.user_message | xml_escape | truncate(512) {{ '}}' }}"
{%- endif %}
{%- endfor %}
    - id: {{ merge.id }}
{%- if creator_step_kind is defined %}
{%- set merge_kind = creator_step_kind(merge.skill) %}
{%- else %}
{%- set merge_kind = "agent" %}
{%- endif %}
{%- if merge_kind in ["skill_exec", "llm_chat"] %}
      kind: {{ merge_kind }}
{%- endif %}
      skill: {{ merge.skill | tojson }}
      read_only: true
      write_access: false
      network_access: false
      depends_on: [{% for b in branches %}{{ b.id }}{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}]
      with:
{%- if merge.with_keys %}
{%- for k, v in merge.with_keys.items() %}
        {{ k }}: {{ v | tojson }}
{%- endfor %}
{%- elif merge_kind == "skill_exec" and merge.skill == "history-explorer" %}
        query: "{{ merge.task }}: {{ '{{' }} inputs.user_message | xml_escape | truncate(512) {{ '}}' }}"
        window_days: "30"
        include: "co_occurrences,meta_usage"
{%- elif merge_kind == "skill_exec" and merge.skill == "git-diff" %}
        mode: cached_fallback_worktree
        cwd: "{{ '{{' }} inputs.workspace_dir | default('.') {{ '}}' }}"
{%- else %}
        task: {{ merge.task | tojson }}
{%- for b in branches %}
        {{ b.id }}_output: "{{ '{{' }} outputs.{{ b.id }} | truncate(2000) {{ '}}' }}"
{%- endfor %}
{%- endif %}
{%- if tail %}
    - id: {{ tail.id }}
{%- if creator_step_kind is defined %}
{%- set tail_kind = creator_step_kind(tail.skill) %}
{%- else %}
{%- set tail_kind = "agent" %}
{%- endif %}
{%- if tail_kind in ["skill_exec", "llm_chat"] %}
      kind: {{ tail_kind }}
{%- endif %}
      skill: {{ tail.skill | tojson }}
      read_only: true
      write_access: false
      network_access: false
      depends_on: [{{ merge.id }}]
      with:
{%- if tail.with_keys %}
{%- for k, v in tail.with_keys.items() %}
        {{ k }}: {{ v | tojson }}
{%- endfor %}
{%- elif tail_kind == "skill_exec" and tail.skill == "history-explorer" %}
        query: "{{ tail.task }}: {{ '{{' }} inputs.user_message | xml_escape | truncate(512) {{ '}}' }}"
        window_days: "30"
        include: "co_occurrences,meta_usage"
{%- elif tail_kind == "skill_exec" and tail.skill == "git-diff" %}
        mode: cached_fallback_worktree
        cwd: "{{ '{{' }} inputs.workspace_dir | default('.') {{ '}}' }}"
{%- else %}
        task: {{ tail.task | tojson }}
        upstream: "{{ '{{' }} outputs.{{ merge.id }} | truncate(2000) {{ '}}' }}"
{%- endif %}
{%- endif %}
---

# {{ name }} (Meta-Skill, P2 fan_out_merge)

{{ description }}

## Execution Flow
{%- for b in branches %}

- Branch `{{ b.id }}` runs `{{ b.skill }}`.
  Purpose: {{ b.task }}
{%- endfor %}

- Merge `{{ merge.id }}` runs `{{ merge.skill }}`.
  Purpose: {{ merge.task }}
{%- if tail %}

- Tail `{{ tail.id }}` runs `{{ tail.skill }}`.
  Purpose: {{ tail.task }}
{%- endif %}

## Expected Output

Return a grounded final deliverable from the branch and merge outputs. Cite the
specific upstream evidence used, keep claims within the user request and
available step outputs, and do not invent missing facts.

## Safety

This proposal is read-only. It does not request file writes, network access, or
destructive operations; every generated step carries explicit `read_only`,
`write_access: false`, and `network_access: false` annotations for gate review.

## Creator Gates

Generated proposals must pass structural lint, scheduler dry-run, positive and
negative trigger smoke tests, highest-tier no-meta acceptance comparison, and
runtime E2E comparison before auto-enable eligibility.

## Fallback

LLM should invoke the branch skills (in parallel where possible), then call the merge skill to aggregate, then optionally call the tail skill.
